      <h1 id="title">Spray Tan</h1>
      <p>For our spray tans, we quickly apply a fine mist containing dihydroxyacetone (DHA) using a spray gun created for sunless tanning. DHA is a food-derived ingredient, which has been approved by the FDA for external cosmetics applications and it's considered non-toxic and non-carcinogenic.
 
      When the solution is applied, it reacts with the amino acids in the outer layer of the skin cells, producing a natural-looking tan. The effect of DHA usually appears within an hour of application of the solution. Maximum color results may take anywhere from 6-8 hours to develop.</p>
    
